While learning about phishing, I was surprised to see how easily attackers can create fake websites and emails that look almost identical to real ones.
It is difficult to identify such scams without careful observation. I realized that many people fall victim because they act quickly without verifying the source
This task helped me understand the importance of checking links, email addresses, and website security before sharing any personal information.
I also learned that awareness is the best way to prevent such attacks.
As a result, I will be more cautious while opening emails and clicking links. 
I will also make sure to verify the authenticity of websites before entering any sensitive information and share this knowledge with others.
